// @run
// @log 3
// @log 7
// First-class functions: `apply` receives a function value and calls it
// indirectly via call_indirect over the function table. `fn` needs no type
// annotation — calling it as `fn(a, b)` infers it is a 2-arg function, and the
// signature is unified against the actual argument at each call site.
function add(a: i32, b: i32) a + b
function apply(fn, a, b) fn(a, b)
print(apply(add, 1, 2))
print(apply(add, 3, 4))
